=Description=

"Olave Nduwanje talks to VUB-researcher Mihnea Tanasescu about his book 'Ecocene Politics'. In this video (20') you'll learn more about the chance (unexpected events), change (lack of stability) and locality (diferentially across the globe) of ecological processes, the terror of Gaia and why hope is not necessary for creating a better future. This interview is part of A Series of More-Than-Human Encounters, a collaboration between VUB Crosstalks and Kaaitheater."


